    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati</strong>&nbsp;<strong>rice</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> water to a pot with a lid&nbsp;and bring to the boil over a high heat, once&nbsp;boiling, add the <strong>kaffir</strong>&nbsp;<strong>lime leaves</strong>, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p> <p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kaffir-lime-leaf-and-yellow-fish-curry/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7 and boil a kettle</p> <p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown&nbsp;</strong><strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kaffir-lime-leaf-and-yellow-fish-curry/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with 2-3 tbsp <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>curry powder</strong> and stir for 30 sec, until the oil and spice form a wet, paste-like consistency</p> <p>Reduce the heat to medium-low, add the <strong>onion</strong> and cook for 5 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kaffir-lime-leaf-and-yellow-fish-curry/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the&nbsp;<strong>green beans</strong>&nbsp;in half</p> <p>Once the <strong>onion</strong> has softened, add the<strong>&nbsp;chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> then cook for a further 4 min</p> <p>Tip: watch the garlic closely to prevent burning!</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kaffir-lime-leaf-and-yellow-fish-curry/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong>, the&nbsp;<strong>green beans</strong>, <strong>fish sauce</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>sugar</strong> to the pan</p> <p>Increase the heat to medium, cover and cook for 7-10 min or until the green beans are tender</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kaffir-lime-leaf-and-yellow-fish-curry/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>fish</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p> <p>Drizzle with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p> <p>Put the tray in the oven for 10 min or until the fish is cooked</p> <p>Tip:&nbsp;your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kaffir-lime-leaf-and-yellow-fish-curry/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the cooked <strong>fish</strong> from the oven and cut each fillet in half lengthways</p> <p>Tip: use the lateral line down the fillet as your guide</p> <p>Remove the green bean pan&nbsp;from the heat and the lid from the pan, then allow to cool briefly</p> <p>Stir in the <strong>Greek-style&nbsp;</strong><strong>yoghurt</strong>, then&nbsp;add the <strong>fish</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kaffir-lime-leaf-and-yellow-fish-curry/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>rice</strong> with the <strong>fish curry</strong> alongside (press the rice into a small bowl and turn out for fancy presentation)</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
